pull_request.title: Adds avx2 implementation for qtesla
pull_request.body:
Adds avx2 implementation for qtesla.

Two things to fix before merge:

- KAT are currently different between portable and avx2, resulting in test failures.
- Some optimized sha3 code is present in the implementation; need to abstract it out into OQS.

repo.name: liboqs
repo.description: C library for quantum-safe cryptographic algorithms

pull_request.title: OQS_SHA3_cshake128_simple4x only defined if both AES and AVX2 instructions available
pull_request.body: Got a bunch of build failures overnight in liboqs and relying applications, related to the function `OQS_SHA3_cshake128_simple4x` not being defined.  After diagnosing, I think it's because the sha3.h file wraps `OQS_SHA3_cshake128_simple4x` in `#if defined ` demanding AVX2 and AES instructions, but the qTesla Makefile only checks for AVX2 instructions before enabling the optimized version.  And unfortunately some of our CircleCI test platforms seem to have AVX2 but not AES.  So I propose just updating the qTesla Makefile to check for AVX2 and AES.  The alternative would be to change sha3.h to only demand AVX2, but I didn't know if the source code for that implementation actually depends on AES instructions or not.
